        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Steve Guminski",
          "email": "stephenx.guminski@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-05-22 12:54:11.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-07-29 00:02:58.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6210 utils: Use C99 initializer in jt_nodemap_modify()",
        "message": "LU-6210 utils: Use C99 initializer in jt_nodemap_modify()\n\nThis patch makes no functional changes.  The long_options struct\ninitializer in jt_nodemap_modify() is updated to C99 syntax.\nIt is renamed to long_opts for consistency.\n\nC89 positional initializers require values to be placed in the\ncorrect order. This will cause errors if the fields of the struct\ndefinition are reordered or fields are added or removed. C99 named\ninitializers avoid this problem, and also automatically clear any\nvalues that are not explicitly set.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Steve Guminski <stephenx.guminski@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I4c1bd5a3aa26c486436ae68d698fd89f8735a7fb\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/27889\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
